text_Original: Coming from someone who isn‚Äôt really a MZ fan, and certainly not a Meta fan at all, I was impressed with this. The tech seems to have come a long way. Accessibility of scanning through smart phones seems like a crucial barrier to overcome. Also, headsets need to get smaller, lighter, and more comfortable to wear for long periods of time. I personally feel a kind of physical and mental fatigue after an hour or so in a VR headset, they get sweaty, and eye strain is a thing for me. I can see the opportunities with this stuff though, pretty cool.

Yes this looks wildly real but that might be counterculture to most young people under 25. It will have to have photo realism with filters to adjust imperfections, lighting, or facial make up people prefer, but also offer detachments like anime avatars of themselves or even be photorealistic animals.

People currently have the option to have GIF or photo avatars for photo representation, yet so many people opt for other images. So many people prefer to be entertained by media than be someone in it.
